main event: Two observers reported seeing two flashing reddish-orange lights in the sky over Manchester, New Hampshire, on February 26, 1966.
interesting points: The lights were first seen climbing rapidly toward the observers before disappearing,The duration of the observation was about 2-3 minutes,There were conflicting reports regarding the characteristics of the lights, as some witnesses described them differently,The analysis indicated that insufficient clarity prevented a positive identification of the objects,The sighting was documented under the U.S. Air Force's Project Blue Book.
witness description: Observers reported the lights were flashing and about the same intensity as stars.
